{
  "texts": [
    "But what if our witnesses suffer from the same delusion?",
    "The odds are less for a mass delusion versus a single one, but how is this certified?",
    "Such problems present a certain degree of undecidability as Goedel noted and are in need of further Goedel Expansions [14] for them to be properly analyzed [15].",
    "These usually come as a set of new axioms that expand the original theory in order to solve those problems, but they create a new \"expanded\" theory that in its own existence creates more problems that are incapable of being solved within the new theory set as well.",
    "Evenly so, for many of them there can never be a definitive answer but, at best, a very good approximation."
  ]
}